# The stone furnace has successfully produced a total of 2 stone bricks, and it is currently in a working state with no stones left to smelt. The furnace still has 9 units of coal remaining as fuel.

# At this point, I can extract the produced stone bricks from the furnace to add them to my inventory. 
# I will proceed to extract the 2 stone bricks from the furnace.

extract_item(Prototype.StoneBrick, target=furnace_info, quantity=2)  # Extract the produced stone bricks from the furnace.
print(f"Inventory after extraction: {inspect_inventory()}")  # Check the inventory after extraction.
print(f"Entities on the map: {get_entities()}")  # Final check on the entities present.
